eam GBhave\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"a strongParis 2024with\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"65 medals\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"the TokyoOlympics\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"the final medal table\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials had set a target of between 50 and 70 medals which was safely achieved as a number of big stars secured Olympic triumph, includingKeely Hodgkinson on the Stade de France track, Alex Yeein a dramatic men's triathlonand three crews on the water at Vaires-sur-Marne as therowers rebounded from a difficult time in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 704, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.999999989285243, \"rank\": 1.0714738593141923e-08, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 745, \"end\": 749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.669993898849174e-19, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 879, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.154558266111545e-15, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Officials\", \"from\